<subSubSection lastPageId="49" lastPageNumber="50" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="48.[151,1437,1465,2030]" lastBlockId="49.[151,1437,151,680]" lastPageId="49" lastPageNumber="50" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,242,1465,1490]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">MALE.</emphasis>
Body length 
<quantity box="[400,491,1465,1490]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.6" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" unit="mm" value="4.6">4.6 mm</quantity>
, wing length 
<quantity box="[649,741,1465,1489]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.8" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" unit="mm" value="3.8">3.8 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[754,825,1465,1490]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Head.</emphasis>
Face moderately concave and very weakly projected antero-ventrally; frontal prominence very weakly developed (somewhat similar to Fig. 
<number box="[1164,1175,1501,1525]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="1.0">1</number>
E). Width of vertex at anterior ocellus:width of head 
<number box="[496,507,1537,1561]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="1.0">1</number>
: 
<number box="[511,555,1537,1561]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="3.7">3.7</number>
; the depth of occipital concavity ca. 
<number box="[971,981,1537,1561]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[993,1007,1537,1561]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="8.0">8</number>
of the width of an eye in dorsal view. Width of face:width of head 
<number box="[481,491,1573,1597]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="1.0">1</number>
: 
<number box="[496,541,1573,1597]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="4.2">4.2</number>
. Face black, pale pollinose. Gena shiny brown. Frons and vertex black, lunula shiny brown, frontal prominence shiny, more posterior parts pollinose, the erect pile short and pale. Occiput dull black. Eye with a large area of enlarged facets at anterior margin. Antenna brown; basoflagellomere dark brown, oval; arista nonpilose. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[405,501,1681,1706]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Thorax.</emphasis>
Colour dull black or partly brown laterally, pale pollinose, the pile scattered, short, adpressed and pale; scutellum semicircular, shiny, with a pair of very short, shorter than scutellum, thin, pale setae at posterior margin. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[388,460,1753,1778]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Wing.</emphasis>
Hyaline, stigma yellow. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[755,819,1753,1778]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Legs.</emphasis>
Pro- and mesoleg yellow, tarsomeres 
<number box="[1268,1282,1753,1777]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="4.0">4</number>
and 
<number box="[1343,1357,1753,1778]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="5.0">5</number>
black. Metaleg: coxa brown; trochanter simple, yellow; femur brown, the basal 
<number box="[973,983,1789,1814]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[994,1009,1789,1814]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="5.0">5</number>
yellowish and a broad annulus on the apical 
<number box="[229,239,1825,1849]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[249,264,1825,1849]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="2.0">2</number>
yellow; tibia without apico-ventral tooth, brownish, the basal 
<number box="[1002,1012,1825,1849]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[1022,1038,1825,1849]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="4.0">4</number>
and an annulus on the apical 
<number box="[1400,1410,1825,1849]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[1421,1437,1825,1849]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="2.0">2</number>
yellow; tarsus dark brown or black. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[554,678,1861,1886]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Abdomen.</emphasis>
Length ratio of tergites I, II, 
<date box="[1004,1133,1861,1886]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
III and IV 
<number box="[1123,1133,1861,1886]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="1.0">1</number>
</date>
:3.0: 
<number box="[1184,1223,1861,1886]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="1.8">1.8</number>
: 
<number box="[1227,1267,1861,1886]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="1.6">1.6</number>
. Tergites shiny black; tergite III with a yellow anterior fascia as wide as 
<number box="[832,842,1897,1921]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[852,868,1897,1921]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="2.0">2</number>
of tergite length, the pile of tergites pale, short, adpressed, becoming longer towards the lateral margin; tergite I with an oblique row of 
<number box="[1165,1206,1933,1957]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3–4</number>
pale setae laterally; sternite IV (
<figureCitation box="[290,373,1969,1994]" captionStart="FIGURE 30" captionStartId="49.[151,250,1412,1434]" captionTargetBox="[199,1386,744,1385]" captionTargetId="figure@49.[188,1398,735,1390]" captionTargetPageId="49" captionText="FIGURE 30. Sphegina (Asiosphegina) sinesmila sp. n. (holotype). A. Genitalia, lateral view; aedeagus and left side cercus marked with broken line. B. Left side surstylus. C. Posterior part of abdomen, ventral view. Scale 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/288426/files/figure.png" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
Fig. 
<number box="[344,373,1969,1993]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="30.0">30</number>
</figureCitation>
C) brown, with short pale pile; sternite VI (
<figureCitation box="[876,959,1969,1994]" captionStart="FIGURE 30" captionStartId="49.[151,250,1412,1434]" captionTargetBox="[199,1386,744,1385]" captionTargetId="figure@49.[188,1398,735,1390]" captionTargetPageId="49" captionText="FIGURE 30. Sphegina (Asiosphegina) sinesmila sp. n. (holotype). A. Genitalia, lateral view; aedeagus and left side cercus marked with broken line. B. Left side surstylus. C. Posterior part of abdomen, ventral view. Scale 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/288426/files/figure.png" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
Fig. 
<number box="[930,959,1969,1993]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="30.0">30</number>
</figureCitation>
C) without a tubercle at posterior margin, black, the pile erect, pale; sternites VII and VIII simple, black, the pile short and pale. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1109,1227,2005,2030]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Genitalia,</emphasis>
<figureCitation box="[1233,1317,2005,2030]" captionStart="FIGURE 30" captionStartId="49.[151,250,1412,1434]" captionTargetBox="[199,1386,744,1385]" captionTargetId="figure@49.[188,1398,735,1390]" captionTargetPageId="49" captionText="FIGURE 30. Sphegina (Asiosphegina) sinesmila sp. n. (holotype). A. Genitalia, lateral view; aedeagus and left side cercus marked with broken line. B. Left side surstylus. C. Posterior part of abdomen, ventral view. Scale 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/288426/files/figure.png" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
Figs 
<number box="[1288,1317,2005,2029]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="30.0">30</number>
</figureCitation>
A, B. Note the slightly asymmetrical surstyli and the very large strongly asymmetrical cerci. The superior lobes are symmetrical. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[303,431,188,213]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">FEMALE.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
